</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Type: space_context_select 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.space_context_select"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.space_context_select">
A <b>space_context_select</b> selects one of the spaces that can be mapped to a maths_space. The spaces that can be selected include, but are not restricted to, <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/>, <express_ref linkend="action_schema:ir_express:action_schema.action"/>, <express_ref linkend="action_schema:ir_express:action_schema.action_method"/>, <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/>, <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.general_property"/>, and <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/>. 

</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Type: value_context_select 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.value_context_select"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.value_context_select">
A <b>value_context_select</b> selects one of the values that can be associated with a maths_value. The values that can be associated include, but are not restricted to, product_definition, action, action_method, shape_aspect, general_property, and representation_item.

</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: compound_maths_space_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.compound_maths_space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.compound_maths_space_context">A <b>compound_maths_space_context</b> is a maths_space_context that is defined by a list of other instances of maths_space_context.

The referenced maths_space is a space of tuples. The maths_space_context for each item in a tuple has the corresponding position in the list.

<example>Consider two different instances of maths_space_context, as follows:

<p>P1:</p> 
<p>the relationship between the 2D set of points on the surface of 'my_product' and R2; and</p> 
<p>P2:</p> 
<p>the relationship between the 1D set of states in 'my_activity' and R. </p>
<p>The relationship between:</p>

<ul><li>the 3D set of set of points on the surface of 'my_product' for the states in 'my_activity'; and></li>
<li>
R3 ,
</li></ul>
is the compound_maths_space_context defined by P1 Â´ P2.
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: compound_maths_space_context  Attribute: components 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.compound_maths_space_context.components"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.compound_maths_space_context.components">
the instances of maths_space_context that are components of the compound_maths_space_context.  <p>A maths_space_context for a single state of a product can be derived from the maths_space_context of the product. In this case the single state shall have a compound_maths_space_context with a components list consisting of a single reference to the maths_space_context of the product.
</p>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: defined_maths_space_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.defined_maths_space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.defined_maths_space_context">
A defined_maths_space_context is a maths_space_context that is defined by reference to a representation_context, unit or both.

<note>A defined_maths_space context can be instantiated as a representation_context_defined_maths_space_context, a unit_defined_maths_space_context or both.
</note></ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context">
A explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context is a maths_space_context that is defined by specifying the instances of maths_value_context that are members of the maths_space_context. 

<note>An explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context can only be specified for a discrete maths_space with a finite number of members.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context  Attribute: members 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context.members"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context.members">members: the instances of maths_value_context that are members of the maths_space_context
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_space_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context">
A maths_space_context is a 1-1 mapping between a physical space and a maths_space that indicates a meaning for the maths_space.</ext_description>
