   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.id">
an identifier for the maths_space_context</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_space_context  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.name">
word or sequence of words by which the maths_space_context is referenced</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_space_context  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.description">
a description of the maths_space_context.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_space_context  Attribute: abstract_space 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.abstract_space"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.abstract_space">
the maths_space that has each member corresponding to one member of the physical_space.

<note number="1">This schema references the ABSTRACT entity type maths_space from ISO 10303-50, but not an entity type that is a SUBTYPE. An Application Module that uses this part of ISO 10303 should reference or define at least one SUBTYPE.</note>

<note number="2">Each of the subtypes of maths_function defined in ISO 10303-50 requires that a maths_space be a tuple_space.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_space_context  Attribute: physical_space 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.physical_space"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.physical_space">
