  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.membership_of_maths_space_context.value_context">
the maths_value_context that is a member of the maths_space_context.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: normalized_maths_space_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.normalized_maths_space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.normalized_maths_space_context">
A <b>normalized_maths_space_context</b> is type of defined_maths_space_context that is defined by a reference physical value.

<p>Let:</p>

<p>p be a physical value;
</p>
<p>
p0 be the reference physical value;
</p>
<p>
v be the maths value.
</p>
<p>
An instance of <b>normalized_maths_space_context</b> specifies that:
</p>
p = p0.v

</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: normalized_maths_space_context  Attribute: normalization_basis 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.normalized_maths_space_context.normalization_basis"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.normalized_maths_space_context.normalization_basis">
the reference physical value that defines the maths_space_context.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: representation_context_defined_maths_space_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.representation_context_defined_maths_space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.representation_context_defined_maths_space_context">
A representation_context_defined_maths_space_context is a defined_maths_space_context that specifies a coordinate system. It is defined by reference to a representation_context.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: representation_context_defined_maths_space_context  Attribute: representation_basis 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.representation_context_defined_maths_space_context.representation_basis"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.representation_context_defined_maths_space_context.representation_basis">
 the representation_context that defines the maths_space_context.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: unit_defined_maths_space_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.unit_defined_maths_space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.unit_defined_maths_space_context">
A unit_defined_maths_space_context is a defined_maths_space_context that is defined by a single unit of measure.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: unit_defined_maths_space_context  Attribute: unit_basis 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.unit_defined_maths_space_context.unit_basis"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.unit_defined_maths_space_context.unit_basis">
the unit that defines the maths_space_context. 

<note>This schema references the SELECT type unit from ISO 10303-41, but not the entity types that are selected by unit. An Application Module that uses this part of ISO 10303 should reference at least one of these entity types.</note>

</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
